Principles

The Developer Console will maintain design and user-experience continuity with existing Sanas portal. The implementation will maximize reuse of the Sanas backend, while the subscription model, billing plans, and feature management framework will remain principally unchanged with few necessary changes.

Important Pre-Read

The target URL for the Developer Console will be console.sanas.ai. The admin panel for the Developer Console will follow a structure similar to Portal v3.

At the top level, Sanas will act as the root folder. Under this, the System Groups will include Enterprise and Self Serve, representing enterprise SDK users and self-serve SDK users, respectively.

At the System Group level, the interface will include two tabs: Accounts and Sanas Members. The Homepage will not be visible for now. The primary role supported will be Sanas Admin, who will have the ability to create accounts on the Developer Console.

There will be no changes to the Invite and Manage Access flows at the Sanas group or System Group level.

A new billing plan will be created to support the MVP requirements of the SDK.

Billing Plan Name: Sanas SDK

The plan will include a start date and end date.

Initially, the plan will not enforce license limits or minute caps.

When subscribed to the billing plan Sanas SDK, the users of the account with a valid API keys shall be able to use all the features available with the billing plan Sanas SDK

For example - If Sanas SDK billing plan comes with AT, NC features and not LT feature, the LT feature cannot be consumed through portal and Sanas SDK billing plan

All events and the usage data will be captured and populated in the UTC timezone



Out of Scope



Billing plan creation and management

Consumption of billing plan

Account deactivation processes

Account deletion workflows

Data deletion and retention policies

No custom roles

