User Journey 2 (Logs into Sanas Developer Console)

As a developer / account admin / customer portal user, I should be able to login to the Sanas developer console to create and manage API keys, view usage data for the billing plan I subscribed

Acceptance Criteria

Login Flow

The developer / console user navigates to console.sanas.ai and enters their email address.

If the account exists, the system sends a 6-digit passcode to the registered email.

If the account does not exist, the system displays the following error:

Error Message:
“Account not found. Your account does not have access to the Sanas Developer Console. Please contact Sanas Support.”

Passcode Email

Subject:
Login to your Sanas Developer Console

Body:

Verify your Sanas Developer Account.

Use the passcode below to complete your login.

This passcode is valid for the next 30 minutes.
Do not share it with anyone.

Passcode Verification

(Aligned with the existing v3 construct)

The passcode expires after 30 minutes

The developer enters the passcode to continue

Outcomes:

Success: Redirects the developer to the Developer Console dashboard

Failure: Displays the error
“Invalid or expired passcode.”

Resend Functionality

(Aligned with the existing v3 construct)

A “Resend Passcode” button is available on the verification screen

The button is disabled for 60 seconds after each passcode is sent

Session Management

(Aligned with the existing v3 construct)

User sessions expire after 7 days of inactivity



