User Journey 4 (Create an API Key)

As a developer, I should be able to create named API keys to authenticate usage of the Sanas SDK.

Acceptance Criteria

Initiate Creation

The developer navigates to the Dashboard

Clicks the “Create API Key” button

API Key Creation Form

Form Fields:

API Key Name

Required

Minimum 3 characters

Maximum 64 characters

All characters allowed

Additional Information:

Expiration Notice:
“This key will expire in 60 days.”

Create Key button

Key Generation

A secure API key is generated upon submission

Format:
sk_{32 random alphanumeric characters}

Expiration:

The key expires 60 days after creation

Success Modal

After successful creation, a modal displays the generated API key.

Contents:

“Your API Key” (full key visible)

Copy button → Copies the key to clipboard

Warning:
“Save this key now. You won't be able to see it again.”

Confirmation Requirement:

Checkbox: “I have saved this key” (unchecked by default) - If the key copied to clipboard (i.e. actioned on copy button) this gets selected without manual user selection

Done button remains disabled until the checkbox is selected

Duplicate Names

Duplicate API key names are allowed

If a key with the same name already exists and is active, the system automatically appends a numeric suffix:

(1), (2), (3), etc.

The suffix applied will be the highest existing suffix for that account and key name + 1.

