User Journey 5 (API Key Management)

As a developer, I should be able to view, manage, and delete my API keys from the Developer Console.

Acceptance Criteria

API Keys Dashboard

The dashboard includes an “API Keys” section displaying all created API keys.

Table Structure

Columns:

Name

Key (masked)

Group

Created At

Created By

Expires At

Status

Actions

Example Row

Production Key | sk_****0987 | India | Jan 15, 2026 | Mar 16, 2026 | Active | Delete

Status Indicators

Each API key displays a status based on its expiration timeline:

Active – More than 7 days remaining before expiration; key is valid

Expiring Soon – Less than 7 days remaining before expiration; key remains functional

Expired – Past the expiration date; key is no longer functional

Delete Functionality

Developers can delete an API key from the Actions column.

Flow:

Click the Delete button next to the desired API key

A confirmation modal appears

Modal Details

Title: Delete this API Key

Message: “This action cannot be undone.”

The API key name is displayed for clarity

Actions:

Cancel – Closes the modal with no changes

Delete – Permanently invalidates the key

On Delete:

The API key is immediately invalidated

The key is removed from the active list

The database performs a soft delete (key retained with a deleted_at timestamp)

Success Message:

“The key has been deleted and is no longer valid for use.”

Sort & Filter

Developers can organize the table using the following options:

Sort By:

Created Date

Expiration Date

Name (alphabetical)

Filter:

Status (default view: All)



